Reasoning: The paper presents query-efficient algorithms for computing minimum cuts in unweighted, undirected graphs without knowing the graph. This problem falls under the category of graph algorithms and data structures, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are all relevant sub-categories. Among these, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely categories as they are directly related to graph algorithms and optimization problems. cs.CG is also a likely category as it deals with geometric algorithms, which can be applied to graph problems. cs.CC and cs.GT are less likely categories, but they may still be relevant as they deal with computational complexity and game theory, respectively, which can be used to analyze the performance of the algorithms presented in the paper.
